---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Training Workshops | Jennifer Chong — Corporate Governance Singapore"
  description="Interactive board governance training workshops — SGX compliance, board effectiveness, gender diversity, PLS-SEM, and governance frameworks. Half-day and full-day sessions."
>

<!-- ===== PAGE HERO ===== -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-label" style="color:var(--gold-light);">Workshops &amp; Education</span>
    <h1>Training Programmes</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Interactive, research-backed workshops for boards, audit committees, and governance professionals. Customised to your organisation's specific needs and context.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== WHY TRAINING ===== -->
<section class="bg-white">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header centered">
      <span class="section-label">Why Training Matters</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">The Case for Board Education</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-3">
      <div class="credential-card fade-up">
        <div class="credential-icon">🎓</div>
        <h4>Research-Grounded</h4>
        <p>Every workshop draws on peer-reviewed research and real-world case studies — not generic templates. Your board gets the latest governance thinking applied to Singapore's context.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="credential-card fade-up">
        <div class="credential-icon">🗣</div>
        <h4>Interactive, Not Lectures</h4>
        <p>All workshops are participatory — group discussions, case studies, Q&amp;A, and exercises tailored to your board's specific challenges and questions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="credential-card fade-up">
        <div class="credential-icon">🎯</div>
        <h4>Singapore-Specific</h4>
        <p>Content is tailored to Singapore's regulatory environment — SGX rules, local business culture, and the specific governance challenges facing Singapore boards.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== BOARD GOVERNANCE WORKSHOPS ===== -->
<section class="bg-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">Board Governance Workshops</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Governance Training for Boards</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Half-day or full-day workshops designed for full boards, committees, or governance teams. $5,000 – $8,000 per session.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-2">

      <div class="training-card fade-up">
        <div class="training-card-header">
          <h3>SGX Compliance Fundamentals</h3>
          <p class="duration">Half-day (4 hours) &nbsp;·&nbsp; Board + Senior Management</p>
        </div>
        <div class="training-card-body">
          <p style="font-size:0.9375rem; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">A practical overview of SGX Code of Corporate Governance requirements and Listing Rules — with direct Q&amp;A on your board's specific situation.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>SGX Code of Corporate Governance overview</li>
            <li>Director independence — definition and practical tests</li>
            <li>Board composition requirements (Rules 710–720)</li>
            <li>Audit committee mandate and best practice</li>
            <li>Common compliance mistakes and how to avoid them</li>
            <li>Live Q&amp;A on your board's specific questions</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="training-card fade-up">
        <div class="training-card-header">
          <h3>Board Effectiveness &amp; Governance Maturity</h3>
          <p class="duration">Half-day (4 hours) &nbsp;·&nbsp; Full Board</p>
        </div>
        <div class="training-card-body">
          <p style="font-size:0.9375rem; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">What separates high-performing boards from compliant-but-ineffective ones? This workshop explores the behaviours and structures behind governance excellence.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>What makes a board truly effective (evidence-based)</li>
            <li>Board composition and committee structures</li>
            <li>Board dynamics and healthy debate</li>
            <li>Measuring and improving board effectiveness</li>
            <li>Governance maturity model — where does your board sit?</li>
            <li>Concrete improvement strategies</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="training-card fade-up">
        <div class="training-card-header">
          <h3>Gender Diversity &amp; Inclusive Leadership</h3>
          <p class="duration">Half-day (4 hours) &nbsp;·&nbsp; Full Board</p>
        </div>
        <div class="training-card-body">
          <p style="font-size:0.9375rem; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">The research-backed business case for diversity, with practical strategies for finding, appointing, and integrating female directors in Singapore's market.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Research evidence: what diverse boards actually achieve</li>
            <li>SGX diversity targets — where you stand and what's required</li>
            <li>Where to find qualified female directors in Singapore</li>
            <li>Unconscious bias in director recruitment</li>
            <li>On-boarding diverse directors effectively</li>
            <li>Building an inclusive board culture</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="training-card fade-up">
        <div class="training-card-header">
          <h3>Risk Management &amp; Board Oversight</h3>
          <p class="duration">Half-day (4 hours) &nbsp;·&nbsp; Board + Risk Committee</p>
        </div>
        <div class="training-card-body">
          <p style="font-size:0.9375rem; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">The board's evolving role in risk governance — from oversight of traditional risks to emerging threats including cyber, ESG, and strategic risk.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Board's role in risk management (vs. management's role)</li>
            <li>Risk committee structure and mandate</li>
            <li>Risk appetite — setting and communicating it</li>
            <li>Risk reporting frameworks</li>
            <li>Emerging risks: cyber, ESG, AI governance</li>
            <li>Making better risk decisions at the board level</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="training-card fade-up">
        <div class="training-card-header">
          <h3>Succession Planning &amp; Leadership Pipeline</h3>
          <p class="duration">Half-day (4 hours) &nbsp;·&nbsp; Board + Nomination Committee</p>
        </div>
        <div class="training-card-body">
          <p style="font-size:0.9375rem; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">How boards should approach succession — for directors, the chair, the CEO, and key executives — with frameworks for building a sustainable pipeline.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Board's role in succession planning</li>
            <li>CEO succession — process and best practice</li>
            <li>Building the executive leadership pipeline</li>
            <li>Diversity in succession planning</li>
            <li>Knowledge transfer and institutional memory</li>
            <li>Singapore-specific considerations</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="training-card fade-up">
        <div class="training-card-header">
          <h3>New Director Orientation &amp; Onboarding</h3>
          <p class="duration">Full-day (6–7 hours) &nbsp;·&nbsp; New Directors</p>
        </div>
        <div class="training-card-body">
          <p style="font-size:0.9375rem; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">A comprehensive orientation programme for newly appointed directors — covering their legal duties, governance obligations, and how to contribute effectively from day one.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Directors' legal duties and obligations in Singapore</li>
            <li>SGX compliance overview for directors</li>
            <li>Understanding financial statements and risk reporting</li>
            <li>How to add value in board meetings</li>
            <li>Committee roles and responsibilities</li>
            <li>Q&amp;A and personalised guidance</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== DATA / RESEARCH TRAINING ===== -->
<section class="bg-white">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">Research &amp; Data Training</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">PLS-SEM &amp; Quantitative Research Workshops</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Specialist training in quantitative research methods for academics, postgraduate students, and research professionals.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-2">

      <div class="training-card fade-up">
        <div class="training-card-header" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a3a6a, var(--navy));">
          <h3>PLS-SEM Fundamentals Workshop</h3>
          <p class="duration">Full-day (7 hours) &nbsp;·&nbsp; Postgraduate / Researchers</p>
        </div>
        <div class="training-card-body">
          <p style="font-size:0.9375rem; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Hands-on introduction to Partial Least Squares Structural Equation Modelling (PLS-SEM) — the method used in leading management and governance research.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>When and why to use PLS-SEM vs CB-SEM</li>
            <li>Measurement model assessment (reflective and formative)</li>
            <li>Structural model evaluation and path coefficients</li>
            <li>Mediation and moderation analysis</li>
            <li>Hands-on SmartPLS exercises with real datasets</li>
            <li>Reporting PLS-SEM results for journal submission</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="training-card fade-up">
        <div class="training-card-header" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a3a6a, var(--navy));">
          <h3>Quantitative Data Analysis for Management Research</h3>
          <p class="duration">Full-day (7 hours) &nbsp;·&nbsp; Postgraduate / Researchers</p>
        </div>
        <div class="training-card-body">
          <p style="font-size:0.9375rem; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Practical workshop on applying quantitative methods to management and governance research — from data collection to analysis to publication-ready results.</p>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Research design for quantitative governance studies</li>
            <li>Survey design and scale development</li>
            <li>Common bias issues and remedies</li>
            <li>Panel data analysis techniques</li>
            <li>Regression analysis and interpretation</li>
            <li>Writing up quantitative findings for publication</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== DELIVERY INFO ===== -->
<section class="bg-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header centered">
      <span class="section-label">Delivery Details</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">How Training Is Delivered</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-3">
      <div class="credential-card fade-up">
        <div class="credential-icon">📍</div>
        <h4>On-Site at Your Premises</h4>
        <p>Delivered at your boardroom or training venue in Singapore. Ideal for full-board sessions where confidentiality and group discussion are priorities.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="credential-card fade-up">
        <div class="credential-icon">💻</div>
        <h4>Virtual (Online)</h4>
        <p>Live, interactive online delivery via Zoom or Teams. Suitable for distributed teams, visiting directors, or when on-site scheduling is challenging.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="credential-card fade-up">
        <div class="credential-icon">🎨</div>
        <h4>Fully Customised</h4>
        <p>All workshops are adapted to your organisation's sector, governance challenges, and current priorities. No generic templates — every session is tailored.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="highlight-box fade-up" style="margin-top:2rem; text-align:center;">
      <h4 style="color:var(--navy); margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Typical Group Size: 5–20 participants</h4>
      <p style="margin:0; font-size:0.9375rem;">Governance training works best in smaller groups that allow open discussion. Larger groups available on request.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== CTA ===== -->
<section class="cta-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Book a Training Workshop</h2>
    <p>Tell me about your board's training needs and I'll propose a customised programme.</p>
    <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content:center;">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Enquire About Training</a>
      <a href="/services" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">View All Services</a>
    </div>
    <div class="cta-contact-row">
      <span class="cta-contact-item">📧 jennifercly@gmail.com</span>
      <span class="cta-contact-item">📞 +65 8577 6630</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>
